<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rival1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rival,</orth> subst. 1) competitor: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 4, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.203" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 203</bibl> (fem.). <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 155</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 122</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.72" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.47" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 47</bibl>. Adjectively: <cit><quote>you are two r. enemies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 4.1.147" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. IV, 1, 147</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>to hold a r. place with one of them,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 174</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) associate, companion: <cit><quote>and now both --s to mock Helena,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 156</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>Horatio and Marcellus, the --s of my watch,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 13</bibl></cit>. cf. <emph>Corrival</emph> and <emph>Rivality.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>